gw.api.json

Class JsonVersion

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.json.JsonVersion
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<JsonVersion>

    public class JsonVersion
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<JsonVersion>
    Schema/mapper versions are of the form: 
       <MAJOR>.<MINOR>[.<OTHER>]*[-<DESCRIPTION>]

     <MAJOR> := <number>
     <MINOR> := <number>
     <OTHER> := <number>
     <DESCRIPTION> := <string>

     Examples: 1.0, 1.0-alpha, 1.0.1, 1.0.1.0-beta
    The entire version, including description, must be a valid portable file name, per FileUtil.isValidPortableFileName(String)
    See Also:
    FileUtil.INVALID_PORTABLE_FILENAME_CHARS

      Version ordering is determined by the following rules (in order of preference): numeric components are compared in order, or a version with fewer numeric components comes first, or a version with no description comes first, or lexicographic comparison of version descriptions (case is significant) Examples: 1.0 < 1.1 (minor numeric component determines order) 1.0 < 1.0.1 (3rd numeric component determines order) 1.0-snapshot < 1.0 (empty description determines order) 1.1-release < 1.1-snapshot (lexicographic comparison of descriptions determines order) 1.0-snapshot < 1.1-release (minor numeric component determines order)

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(@NotNull
                     @NotNull JsonVersion v)
        Version ordering is determined by the following rules (in order of preference):
        1. numeric components are compared in order, or
        2. a version with fewer numeric components comes first, or
        3. a version with no description comes first, or
        4. lexicographic comparison of version descriptions (case is significant)
        Examples:
        • 1.0 < 1.1 (minor numeric component determines order)
        • 1.0 < 1.0.1 (3rd numeric component determines order)
        • 1.0-snapshot < 1.0 (empty description determines order)
        • 1.1-release < 1.1-snapshot (lexicographic comparison of descriptions determines order)
        • 1.0-snapshot < 1.1-release (minor numeric component determines order)
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<JsonVersion>
        Parameters:
        v - JsonVersion to be compared
        Returns:
        a negative integer, zero, or a positive integer as this JsonVersion is less than, equal to, or greater than the specified JsonVersion.
